mergeSymmetryMolecules

public CMLMolecule mergeSymmetryMolecules(CMLMolecule mergedMolecule,
                                          Contact contact,
                                          int serial,
                                          Transform3 orthMat)
uses the atoms in a contact to merge molecules. the molecules containing the from- and to- atoms are found with getMolecule() and the symmetry operator is applied to these. Then any overlapping atoms are removed.

Parameters:
mergedMolecule - molecule which grows as new atoms are added
contact -
serial - number of contact (to generate unique id)
orthMat -
addBonds - if true add additional bonds
Returns:
molecule a molecule composed of the merged molecules
